summary:
The Security Council, having considered the report of the Secretary-General on the United Nations Disengagement Observer Force, reaffirms its resolution 1308 (2000) and:

1. Calls upon concerned parties to implement immediately its resolution 338 (1973);
2. Welcomes efforts by the United Nations Disengagement Observer Force to implement the Secretary-General's zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse, requests the Secretary-General to continue taking necessary action, and urges troop-contributing countries to investigate and punish such acts;
3. Decides to renew the mandate of the United Nations Disengagement Observer Force for six months, until 31 December 2007;
4. Requests the Secretary-General to submit a report on developments and measures taken to implement resolution 338 (1973) at the end of this period.
